svg.text: Easy Access to Internet Remains a Distant Dream for many Americans
Despite living in the richest country in the world, many Americans do not have access to internet from their home

Nearly all Southern states fail to cross 65% home internet access rate
with West Virgina, Missisipi and Loiusiana even being below 60%

svg.text: Source: United States Census Bureau, Current Population Survey, October 2012

text.tspan: Note: According to the Current Population Survey of 2012, only 69.1% of Americans could access Internet from their home. This number varied by state
with coastal states generally performing the best. However, no state has yet been able to cross 80%. Southern states in particular lag behind the rest of America
